This Is the last entry I will be writing in this journal... i got a new one and it isn't livejournal so if you want to read you are going to have to click on the link in my profile.... thank you and have a nice day.

All anyone ever wants is to be happy... am I right.  No one sets out doing something saying to themselves I am doing this to be miserable... it just doesn't work that way.


Well all I wanted was to be happy and I thought it was going to make me happy and I guess I though it was or at least was for a short time.  But now that I sit here and look back on the whole situation I come to realize I was never really happy.  I guess I though by making you happy it would make me happy but all it did was make me miserable, miserable may be to strong of a word but sad isn't a strong enough word.  Somewhere in the middle I guess is where i am.  I sit here and laugh about everything in the past but all I really want to do is cry.  Why would I ever think it was the right thing, I guess I was just hoping and holding on to a little piece that everything would turn out great in the end. I knew it would never but a girl can dream can't she... thats all it really was a dream that would never and could never come true.  I hate the fact that I let myself be in that situation, it is something I swore to myself that I was better than, well not better than but atleast strong enough emotioanlly to stay away from. But when push came to shove I wasn't very strong at all.  I guess it is easy for one to sit there and tell themselves that they will never put themselves in that situation but what one says and what one does sometimes are two totally different things.  And you really don't know how something will effect you until it actually happens.  I can sit here and say I am through with the whole thing and that I have learned my lesson but I don't know if I am or if I really have learned my lesson.

OK so last Night was the Matchbook Romance, Maxeen, The Matches Show and it was awesome.... by far one of the best show I have been to in a really long time.  When we first got there we though it was canceled or something because there was like no one there.. it was crazy... so first we are thinking ok not that many cars this mean a lot of little 12 year olds.  So we go inside and it was like empty.  It was great hardly anyone there so there was actual breathing room.  

So first on was this band Gibbler that I had never heard of... the were pretty good there a local band so that was cool.  Than it was the Matches who put on an awesome set.  The Shawn is so crazy on stage it was great.  Then Maxeen was on another great set. Tom is so trying to be sting though but it is ok but he can pull it off and pull it off very well.  So after Maxeen finished we went and walked around where we got to meet Shawn from The Matches.. awsome guy real funny too.  The we went to the merch table to see what they had and we got to meet Shannon from Maxeen also really cool we talk to him for like 20 mins.  

Then it was time to go watch Matchbook Romance.... they are so good live.. I loved it.  They played a few new songs which was cool and they played Tiger Lily which made me very happy because it is my favorite song.  Oh yeah and I love how he made fun of bands that call themselves EMO.  It was great he had a good point though.  If Emo is short for emotion and emo bands write about emotion then all bands are emo because all song are written with some kind of emotion about some kind emotion.  

So after the show we were leaving and we meet up with Shannon from Maxeen again he introduces us to Jay the Drummer so after we talk to them we are walking away and they totally scream out the door to say by to us. So when we get outside Shawn, Matt, and Jon from the Matches are there playing on acoustics.  So we stay and watch them for awhile then when they stopped playing we stayed for awhile and talked.  They seem like they would be so much fun to just chill with.  Well then it was home and now here I am writing in here once again.

Ok this summers shows are as followed:

Matchbook Romance w/Maxeen & The Matches 6/4

Fall Out Boy w/ Anberlin, Don't look down, & Punchline 6/18

Warped Tour 8/8

Going to be a fun summer well atleast those three dates...

Ok so the past few days have been a whirl wind of emotions... I got in a huge fight with my parents about school and work and of course because they will never admit they are wrong and I won't either and they refuse to see things from my point of view and me from theirs I got very upset and defensive and so did they.  The fight ended with me car less and not returning to Rider next year.  Now when I was told to forget about going back to Rider I had mixed emotions about this.  Now for you rider people reading this don't get mad at me.  I was actually kind of happy that they told me I couldn't go back, but at the same time I was devastated.  You have to understand a few things. The only thing that makes me want to go back is my friends, I have been thinking about this for a while now and as much as I love being there and around everyone the whole class thing just doesn't seem to be for me.  I don't even know if I am in the right major.  I start to think if I should have just done what my parents wanted from the beginning and gone to arts school.  Photography is something I love doing, I love being the the dark room for hours developing pictures.  Getting it how I want it.  That was the one thing in High School that not matter how shitty I was feeling all I had to do was go in the dark room and work on my pictures and it seemed to make everything better.  It is kind of like an escape from reality. I know most parents don't want their kids in art school because there is no definite future in it but thats where they wanted me.    Now I don't want anyone to think I regret going to Rider because I wouldn't change the friendships I have made for anything.  I am just confused in what I want out of life.  And I know I have been bitchy lately and I am sorry but I am just trying to deal with everything and figure out what is best for me and what I really want to do.  Well so back to the fight with the parents after a couple days of not knowing what to say to them and them not knowing what to say to me we finally talked about things and I am returning to Rider next year.  So no need to worry anymore about the apartment girls because we can still have it.

Right so I am at work... no big surprise there.  Lucky me I get to work with my mo today ah joy... she is such a pain.  She has to make a major project out of the smallest stuff... This still being sick is really getting to me... i just want to feel better is that really to much to ask.

So yeah i miss being at rider and I miss all the people that I would hangout with but you all know this already because well I have either told you or put it in here... but there is one person I miss hanging out with that I haven't told and well i probably shouldn't miss hanging out with and I am really trying not to but so far it isn't going so well.  I never really hung out with this person that much but the times we did were always fun and I miss that.  I guess one reason I think I miss hanging out with them so much is because I know that I will never get to hangout with them again since last year was their last year at Rider.  I don't even know if you read this but if you do I just wanted to let you know that the past year was a lot of fun and I am glad that I got to know you and spend the time I did with you.... well i guess thats it for now

So last night almost all the Evil's came down and we went out to dinner... Shannon you were missed.

So we went to Pete & Elda's because Kevin and Bryan had never been and well everyone who lives in Jersey should go there at least once.  So Kevin got his "whole pie eaters club" Shirt.  Good job (even if you didn't eat the whole thing). After dinner we went back to my house and well we just sat around and talked.  Oh yeah and well I don't know if it was such a great idea but Bryan got Boots the talking Monkey... I hope he doesn't piss Kevin off to much next semester at school... There are RULES for that thing Bryan... you have to follow them I promised Kevin you would. Oh yeah we all went to D&D... it wasn't the same because the guy didnt have our coffee ready for us when we walked in but it was still fun.. I haven't been to D&D since I left school.  I showed everyone some creepy tent things in Ocean Grove that Shannon and I found the last time we hungout... weird little things.

I love the Evils... you guys are the best... I couldn't have asked to find better friends at Rider.  I wish we could all hangout more during the summer but it's hard because we all work and live so far apart... but I guess it's ok because next semester we will either be roomies or we will only be a walk up or down the stairs from each other.

Right so yesterday was monday and I was suppose to go into work at 9 b/c it is my mom's day to open and then I go in later and get to go and ride around on the cart all day and see if I can get the golfers anything... now yesterday when I woke up I still wasn't feel well at all. I was actually feeling worse than I had any other day so I asked If i could stay home a rest.  So I guess after 30mins she finally said ok and this is only because I talk to my dad and he talk to her.  So I spent the whole day in bed.  I guess around 5ish my dad got home and he made me dinner because I hadn't eaten all day because I couldn't and then he left to go out and i went back to sleep.  So then I am guessing around 8ish I don't really know because I didn't look at a clock I woke up with the worst migraine ever.  So i went down stairs and looked at my mom who was looking a little blurry because I couldn't see straight it was so bad and I asked her for something that I could take.  She just looked at me and then continued to watch tv... HELLO.... EXCUSE ME!!!! she just totally ignored me what the hell so me not being able to see straight and I couldn't look at the light because it hurt to much went back upstairs to my room where it was nice and dark... now for those reading this that haven't known me that long when I get a migraine I can't be in a lighted room and I need complete silence and I usually can't see anything because everything is blurry.(sounds fun doesn't it).  So All of a sudden my dad comes running up the stairs to see what the hell is wrong with me because after my mom ignored me I yelled at her and was "thanks for caring".  So he went and got me something to take for it and gave me an ice bag to but on my head because I was burning up.... yes well that was my wonderful day off of work yesterday....
YAY!!!!!!!!!!!!    so yeah I have heard from everyone and everyone is down for wed. night... i am so excited now I can't wait.

Ok so i'm sick and well since there is no one around to listen to me complain I am going to do it in here.

Today sucked to no end... nothing good happened or came out of it.

First I wake up at 3am because I can't breathe and I can't stop coughing.  Then I finally stop coughing but I can't get back to sleep so I curled up under my blankets and just stayed in bed until my my alarm went off at 4:15... than i got up and got ready and was at work by 5am.  So while at work I think I coughed up a lung, had a headache all day, and I went through almost a whole box of tissues. Right so not that being sick and at work is enough to make someone misurable.... no I had to get random nose bleeds... what the hell could something else go wrong and could I feel any shitter....  I hate being sick so much all I want is someone to take care of me and bring me soup but it doesn't look like that is going to happen.... :(

so off i must go.. it's time to try the whole sleep thing considering I got to be at work at 5am again tomorrow

They where right when they said that it wasn't something they saw me doing.  It just would have been nice to have them backing me maybe if I knew they believe in me I would have done better. Yeah so once again i am at work and bored....  This tends to be a trend with me....  and it isn't like there is nothing to do at work it is just that work sucks... it isn't fun at all. And I also think it is boring because it is so repetitive and the hours are so long.  I sat down a figured out how much I work in a week and I almost cried.

Sat 5am-7pm
Sun 5am-7pm
Mon 9am-7pm
Tues 6am-6pm
Wed Off
Thur Off
Fri 9am-7pm

Yeah so that is 60hr a week.... right so this summer is going to so much fun.

To some it is only goodbye until one of us gets our ass in our car a drives to the others house to hangout, to some it's goodbye until next semester and to others it is goodbye forever.... I always hate goodbyes and some are harder than others but some are needed.  There are some people that I know I have to say bye to even though I may not want to or be ready to.  I know some of the ones leaving forever I will probably still talk to every once in awhile on line but it isn't the same as running into them in daly's or while walking to class.... to the people I have gotten close with this past semester you know who you are.  The friendships we have built mean the world to me and it is going to suck that I can't just wake up and walk across the hall and hangout with you or walk down to c-wing.  I am going to miss the late nights every night, the random road trips to different places at 4 in the morning, board games, roller blading(don't judge), the fact that we drive 20 minutes to get D&D, the great talks and the funny conversations.... I guess I am pretty much just going to miss everything and everyone.... love you guys we have to try and get together as much as we can this summer because I am going to be going through withdraw of you guys and I will need my fix of the FAILURE moments and DON'T JUDGE actions.

I FAIL AT LIFE ONCE AGAIN!!!  

*hanging my head in shame*

Can some one just answer me this.... why do I always end up hurting the ones I love... why do I continue to put my self in the same situations that I know are always going to end the same... why can't I tell people how I really feel... 

Listen up people this is to everyone that I have hurt and caused pain to.  I'm sorry I never meant to, trust me. I know in some cases it is to late for a sorry and sorry isn't even close to what you deserve but It's all I got.  I am especially sorry for the pain I have cause the people who are closest to me I love you guys with all my heart even though some of you haven't been in my life all that long you guys are my world.

Right so I am sitting at work bored to no end....  I got up at 4:30am and well my friends back at school hadn't even gone to bed yet.... this whole working before the sun comes up sucks.  I mena really folks I work at a golf course you can't really golf before the sun is up.  So why I ask you do I have to be here so frickin early.  

Yeah there hasn't been much to write in here. My whole week seems to consist of doing the same things every night we take road trips, we go to D&D and  Denny's, and play board games.  I really need a change here folks.  Don't get me wrong I love doing these things but If I don't start doing something different I am going to start to hate doing these things.

Yeah so You all know I work for my parents and well this would seem like a good thing except for the fact that they don't pay me.  I do get tips though so I do have some form of income.  So yeah my mom made a deal with me.  I give her $10 everyday I work and she puts it in an account for me that I can't touch until the end of the summer and what ever I have at the end she will match.  This way I will have money for the time when the cafe is close in the winter.  And since I will be living in the apartment next year and I won't have a meal plan at Daly's she figures this could be my money for food shopping and stuff for the apartment.  Yeah so on top of giving her $10 each day I work I am saving all my change and I am going to try to put and extra $20 a week away just so I have spending cash.  Ok well this is my plan for saving now all I have to do actually save which always seems to be my problem.  I am trying to think of it this way if I work 5 days a week for 4 months that means I give my mom $50 and she puts in $50 so if I do that for 4 months thats  $1600 then by me putting and extra $20 aside thats another $320, then all my change.  Ok  have a goal now and it is to go back to school with $2000 saved.

Oh ok on a side note about the apartment.... Lauren and Michelle my mom said she has a coffee table we could have and a end table I don't know if you guys want them just let me know so I can let her know if she should keep them or not.

Drama loves me... I have come to this conclusion.  So I am also come to the conclusion that I am just going to stay out of everything from this point on.  I don't want to be in the middle of everyone elses problems.  Don't bring me into them I don't care... deal with them on your own.  If you have a problem with someone don't bring me into I am tired of trying to fix things because it always back fires on me and them you end up being mad at me instead of the person you actually have the problem with.  And to make it fair I won't bring anyone into my problems.  I will deal with them on my own this way I won't hurt anyone that does not need to be hurt.   

The end of the school year is coming up very quickly and there are so many things that have gone unsaid and probably will continue to go unsaid. Which is a shame but I guess thats the way life is.  Maybe it is for the best, maybe certain things are meant to be kept to one's self, maybe in time it won't make a difference if they were not said or maybe in time I will realize that things could have been better if I would have just had the nerve to say what I was feeling.  I really don't like all these what if's and maybe's in my life and I know I could change that if I just would tell people what was on my mind and what was wrong and how I was feeling but it isn't as easy as it sounds so until I figure out how to do so I will just have to deal.

So I am home once again so I can work the whole weekend... I hate being home.  I have no one to hangout with so I am not only bored but I am bored all by myself.

So my Birthday week kicked ass.... Love you guys.  I got to hangout with Amanda a lot this week because she came up to visit me and ended up spending 4 days... which was very cool because since I went away to college we don't get to hangout all that much.  So yeah Amanda finally got to meet all the people I am always telling her about and she loved them all which is really cool.  She got to see what we do at Rider.  

So yeah there is this exit on 195 that I always pass and it has always interested me because the name on the sign says "COX CORNER"  So one night we were on one of our road trips and we decide to see what it was.  Yeah can we say weird and scary.  It is like a 2 mile dirt road in the middle of the woods.  So yeah once we finally got off the dirt part we were in like farm country.  We almost hit Bambi like 4 times.  So of course the next night we ventured back to Cox Corner.  We also ended up going to Asbury Park to walk around... fun stuff let me tell you.  One day I want to go back while the sun is up so I can take pictures.  Asbury may not be the pretty place but if you take the time to really look at it, it has some really nice buildings.  It by far is my favorite place to take black & Whites of.

To Lauren thanks for making me talk about what was bothering me... I felt better after our talk.  

To Lauren and Michelle our roommate bonding time was great.  Our apartment is going to rock next year I can't wait to live with you two..... you know it just won't be us to living their either... I have a feeling we will always be having someone on the futon.

I Love my friends.... thanks for the best birthday ever. And I really mean it you guys made my 20th birthday so memorable. 

I just want to thanks everyone for the awesome gifts... To Brea and Dan the devils blankets Rocks I luv it... To Dana For getting me my very own Monkey... To Amanda who thinks I am an alcoholic thanks for the 5 shot glasses and the tower shot... To Bryan for my Doozer I love her it's exactly what I wanted your the bestest... to Kevin for my Care bear cousin now my other care bear has a friend... To Derio for the LTJ shirt they are my favorite band....  To Lauren my sticker rocks and thanks for helping Derio pick out his gift.... To Shannon I luv my crabby straw.... To Michelle I love the little monkey you got me and the monkey belt  they are awsome.... Jen thats for the scratch off's you know I am addicted to them.... Tracy thanks for the cash you just being able to be here was gift enough though....  To Mike thanks for coming up for the night... I love all of you with all my heart you guys are my world and I would not be able to make it through my time here at Rider and at home with out you.  You guys are the one good constant thing in my life and that means everything to me

Oh yeah Lauren, Michelle and I got the Kroner C-wing Apartment.... yay... this means no more daly's food b/c we get out own Kitchen.

Right so this week went by rather fast... Went on a few small road trips like we do every week.  You know the ones I am talking about... where we either travel 20 mins to the Dunkin Donuts because some believe it has the better coffee or we go to someones home town and do something.  Ok so just some things I though were funny from these trips

  • The bunny on the side of the road that looked like it was going to eat small children & the scream that came from Lauren when she saw it
  • There is no nice way to say this guys....
  • I have a text message... oh yeah I forgot I text myself.
  • Padital... motorcycle.
  • The fights over the front seat.
  • The little spastic Kitten and the puppy who kept running into the glass.
  • He shall be mine... I shall call him Sobe... He shall be my little Sobe...(the little bunny who lives by the basketball courts)

Ok well that was some stuff from out little road trips... Now on to tell you all about our Road trip to Six Flags America in Maryland.  Ok since there was Five of us and we all drive little cars so we had to take two cars. And so we could all talk on the trip each car had a walky Talky.  In my car was Lauren, Michelle and me.  Then the was Kevin and Bryan in Kevin's car.  So we left school around 9am I guess and set out on our adventure.  So first we stopped for gas and as we were sitting in the parking lot waiting for Lauren to get her coffee we start throwing a bouncy ball back and forth between the two cars.  As I throw it at Kevin's car and It bounce off the car and into the major highway two cop cars pull into the gas station.  Right so we are thinking oh shit were going to get in trouble and we haven't even really started the trip yet.  But it was all good they just drove right by us.  Ok so back to the road.... we drove for what seems like forever when we see all this black smoke in the air.  So we are trying to figure out what it is and where it is coming from.  So we seem to be getting closer to it and first we thing a car blew up or somethings like that.  Then we drive past a wooded area and see that all the trees are on fire.  Yeah so we took pictures because how often do you get to see a forest fire.  Also on our way there was saw the pretty Mustang so of course we took pictures of it.  Yeah the guy driving the truck that was carrying the Mustang had a Mullet which made it oh so much cooler.  Ok so we finally after like 4 hours of driving get the Six Flags.  The time we spent in the park was a lot of fun we got to go on some different rides and we played a few games.  So one of the last things we did before we left the park was go to the show that the characters put on and while we were there we saw Griffin's twin... well the hispanic version of him anyway.  This kid had his straight jacket, black shirt and pants, black boots, his hair, he was even carrying a cd player around with him... Kind of creepy to think there is more than one of them out there.  So much for him being an original person.  So we get back in our cars and start to head back home.  We get this bright idea to play car tag which was interesting.  Lauren explains the game to us like this.  Two or more cars through food or what ever they can at each other while driving, you get more points if the window is open and you hit the person. So of course you know being the mature group that we are we play the game.  I believe the final score was girls 3 boys 2.  And best hit goes to Lauren for her peanut butter cup throw that hit Kevin's windshield. Ok so that game ended when the boys ran out of stuff to throw.  Then it was just pretty much quit driving time with a few things said every once in awhile.  Yeah so the radio picked up some girl saying that the Peter Pan bus was being pulled over so we of course are looking for this bus.  About 2 hours later we found it.  Then finally we were back at school and it was time for everyone to get back in their cars and head home.  All that is except for Bryan who is at Rider all by himself today... poor guy.  Yeah so that was the road trip the edited version.... I am sure a lot more funny stuff happened but considering it is only 7:30 in the am and I had to be up at 4:30 am today I am still not that awake and to remember more would take effort and I just can't do that this early in the morning.  Guys I had a great time yesterday... we need to have more road trips with a destination.  And maybe next time we find a bigger car than a mustang so we can all travel in the same car.  No wait I take that back two cars was fun the whole car tag and walky Talky thing made it that much more fun.  Oh yeah I put the pics from the trip on the picture page so go check them out.

yeah so not much going on in my life.... I did though go on a little road trip last night.  So here is a short recap of the trip.... took a detour got lost in the maze of a town.  Finally got out and ended up in farm country where I saw a tractor crossing sign (I want it).  We finally get back to the road that we started on and continued on our way... I get pulled over for doing 35 in a 25 but the cop was nice she wrote me a ticket for Failure to obey signs which is only a $47... not that bad. ok so the weekend was pretty boring... I worked... oh joys so much fun not really.  Once again I didn't go to work at the diner sunday night.
